com.thinkaurelius.titan.core.schema

Interface TitanSchemaType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Namifiable, TitanSchemaElement
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EdgeLabel, InternalRelationType, InternalVertexLabel, PropertyKey, RelationType, SystemRelationType, VertexLabel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseKey, BaseLabel, BaseRelationType, BaseVertexLabel, EdgeLabelVertex, EmptyRelationType, ImplicitKey, PropertyKeyVertex, RelationTypeVertex, VertexLabelVertex

    public interface TitanSchemaType
extends TitanSchemaElement
    A TitanSchemaType is a TitanSchemaElement that represents a label or key used in the graph. As such, a schema type is either a RelationType or a VertexLabel.

    TitanSchemaTypes are a special TitanSchemaElement in that they are referenced from the main graph when creating vertices, edges, and properties.

    Author:
    Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)
